# Components

Conventions for React components in `src/components/`, `src/providers/`, and reusable UI.

## Core rules

- **Functional components only** — no class components.
- **PascalCase** for component names and file names (e.g. `BookCard.tsx` exports `BookCard`).
- **Named exports** — `export function BookCard`, not `export default`.
- **Props interface above the component** — name it `{ComponentName}Props`.

## Server vs client

- **Server Components by default** — no `'use client'` unless the component needs interactivity, state, effects, or browser APIs.
- Add `'use client'` as the first line when required.


## Next.js route files

`src/app/**/page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx`, and `not-found.tsx` **must** use default exports per Next.js. Apply these conventions to the component body and props typing; the default export is the only exception.


## Organization

- One primary component per file; co-locate small helpers used only by that component.
- Put reusable components in `src/components/`; app-wide providers in `src/providers/`.
- Import with `@/` path aliases.
